There really are no words to describe how much I love uburger... but, I definitely have to say that the service and attitude of the people that work here is one of the things that makes me feel really comfortable and happy when I go here.  The fries are great! They are everything you'd want and expect in a french fry, but uburger puts a slightly unique spin on them that really makes them stand out. They're very fresh tasting and are fried to just the right amount of crispiness.  Normally I'm pretty intimidated by predesigned burgers, but don't shy away from theirs!! They have some really great combinations! Their chicken sandwiches are also amazing, if you're not in the mood for a burger.  Most of the time, I place an online order to pick up. They are very prompt and timely about getting my order done on time, which I greatly appreciate because not enough places are respectful about this.  Wish I could give them more than five stars!!

You have to try their sweet potatoe fries, a large serving is more than enough to share as a side or enjoy as a treat all by your self. My girlfriend and I went to Uburger today to check out their grand re-opening--everything was 50% off! I got a Club Chick (opted for grilled chicken, shredded lettuce, mayo, tomato, Swiss cheese, no bacon). I also ordered their new sweet potato fries. My total (with the 50% discount) was 5.08--unreal!  The food was ready in about 5 minutes and I was really impressed with the presentation of the sandwich. They wrap them in individual wrappers that seem to trap the heat. Very nice touch!  The small sweet potato fries was more than enough for 1, and possibly could feed 2 people. They were great--thin, crispy on the outside and soft on the inside. Very filling!  As for the sandwich, the chicken was super tender and juicy (a bit messy on a bun), and the bun was so soft! I could have done without the mayo and I was disappointed to find shredded lettuce when the menu says "lettuce." While technically not false advertising, I expected romaine lettuce from a burger place.  Overall the staff was super quick and helpful. The place is somewhat small, and was pretty crowded for the re-opening. However, it has a very young vibe considering all of the college kids that frequent it. It also has really cool outlets that have USB chargers in case you need to charge your phone.  I would definitely check it out again!

A+ across the board! We have been going to uBurger since they opened their first location in Kenmore 5 years ago. We have known the owner Nick since the day they opened. He is as solid as they come, and their burgers are incredible! I actually mixed it up last night and went with their garden salad with grilled chicken, at their Commonwealth Ave. location, and it was also phenomenal.  They make their salads fresh twice daily, so the lettuce was outstanding, veggies fresh, and the grilled chicken was mouth watering.  And I am very picky with salads. You can't go wrong here.  I prefer the Yuppy Burger with swiss cheese, mushrooms and bacon, and I order an extra patty for a $1.  No-brainer! :) As we were walking out the owner Nick offered us free milkshakes to thank us for being such loyal customers.  Just a great great guy. I have literally stopped going to restaurants based on an owner being cold. Nick should write a book on how to treat customers. Support this local business! They are the best burgers in town, and just a great group of employees, who help make our overall experience an A+ every time we walk through the doors. Thank you, uBurger!
